gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Hawks 134, Rockets 127
gameRecap.excerpt: The Hawks defeated the Rockets, 134-127. Trae Young recorded his fifth consecutive game with 30+ points and 10+ assists as he tallied 30 points (5-8 3pt. FG) and 14 assists for the Hawks, while Bogdan Bogdanovic added 22 points and four 3PM in the victory. Jabari Smith Jr. notched a career-high 34 points, along with 13 rebounds for the Rockets in the losing effort. The Hawks improve to 12-15 on the season, while the Rockets fall to 13-12.
